reviewText: I'd give it five stars if it weren't for the frenetic editing. It changes shots every three seconds & often focuses on a player when he isn't playing yet the audio indicates that he is.
Shipping was quick, 3 days. And the quality of the video was great!

A high point in terms of the Stones performance, but also one of the better videos in terms of editing.  The camera captures all of the musicians at relevant moments in contrast to some past videos which tended to follow Jagger exclusively.  Having Taylor on stage was a treat.  Jagger was at his best - great harmonica work as well.  Richards was fantastic.  Woods, Watts, Keys, and the rest were tight.
I am 68yrs old I was in England in 1969 these guys have been rocking out all these years and have never failed to put on a good concert. Great concert well worth seeing.
Shows them at there best. Love to see the old rockers aging gracefully, and still the best at what they do.
Awesome concert...feel like I am catching up with all the concerts I was unable to attend...next best thing to actually being there!

What a great show I remember when the band was just a rhythm and blues band and just stood there and played songs. The Rolling Stones have really grown over the years and learned how to put a show on but the basic elements of the band are still there the rock n roll and blues roots. Mike Taylor was a nice add to the show and was very special and Mick Jagger's vocal are better then ever
they are old but still great
Excellent concert DVD - somewhat of a documentary which just adds to the concert experience!  Definitely a must for any Rolling Stone collection!
